definition: to disappear/to vanish/to eliminate/to spend (time)/have to/need
to lift a prohibition/to lift a ban

sentences.english: All eastbound trains have been cancelled due to faulty signals.
sentences.chinese: 所有向东开去的火车由于信号错误而均被取消。

sentences.english: We know they are keen to see sanctions lifted.
sentences.chinese: 我们知道他们渴望看到制裁被取消。

sentences.english: Registratie ongedaan maken van de User Account Control Support Library is mislukt.
sentences.chinese: 取消用户账户支持运行库失败。

sentences.english: This regular meeting has been sublated.
They also welcomed the decision to cancel the run-off election.
sentences.chinese: 他们也对阿富汗取消决选表示欢迎。

sentences.english: The Chinese Exclusion Act was repealed only in 1943.
sentences.chinese: 直到1943年排华法案才被取消。

sentences.english: Ecclestone said at the Abu Dhabi Grand Prix at the weekend that he had doubts about whether the race would happen.
sentences.chinese: 伯尼说这周末举行的阿布扎比大奖赛也可能被取消。

sentences.english: Our visit abroad has been cancelled due to some special reasons.
sentences.chinese: 由于特殊原因，我们这次外访活动被取消了。

sentences.english: Canceling or not bidding on selected projects or contracts.
sentences.chinese: 取消或者不竞标被选定的项目或合同。

sentences.english: The centre reserves the right to cancel a programme if there is insufficient number of enrollments.
sentences.chinese: 如报读人数不足，本中心有权取消有关课程。

sentences.english: To force the cancellation or postponement of(an outdoor event) because of rain.
sentences.chinese: 板球比赛因天雨而取消。

sentences.english: Scholarships will be canceled for those who cannot pass the health examination.
sentences.chinese: 入学体检不合格者，奖学金资格将被取消。

sentences.english: The omission of heat straightening may save energy and thus reduces production cost.
sentences.chinese: 特别是取消热调直可节约能源，从而降低生产成本。

sentences.english: I was going to see Mrs. Ked the next day, but the appointment has been cancelled.
sentences.chinese: 我本打算第二天去看基德先生，但是约会被取消了。

sentences.english: Please countermand our order for same.
The label could be rescinded if the data is not produced, the officials said.
sentences.chinese: 官员们说，如果不提供数据，将取消称号。

to repeal (a law)/to put an end to/abolition/annulled
to convert/to turn into (sth else)/to adapt (a story to another medium)
to become invalid/to cancel/to delete/to nullify
newly added/additional/to add (to what already exists)
